This paper discusses the evaluation of risk factors for software vulnerabilities, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR) and software engineering (cs.SE). The methodology proposed in the paper involves statistical analysis, which could fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) or data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of black markets to assess the risk of exploits, which could be related to cybercrime (cs.CY).
